Sausage, potato, and vegetable hash is a delicious dish that can be prepared in just 15 minutes. You can add desired veggies like broccoli and carrots to make it more healthy. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 In a large pan heat oil over medium heat. Then sauté the baby potatoes until golden seasoning with salt and pepper then set aside. Step 2 In the same pan, add a little oil and brown the smoked sausage. Step 3 Add garlic, onion, and bell pepper to the sausages. Cook for 2 to 3 minutes until softened. Step 4 (optional) Add a little water and stir to coat the smoked sausage and veggies and create a thick sauce. Step 5 Add the sautéed potatoes back to the pan and mix everything to reheat the potatoes. Step 6 Serve on a plate and garnish with chopped fresh Dhania and enjoy.